==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pathway
<hw>Path"way</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A footpath; a beaten
track; any path or course. Also used figuratively.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In the way of righteousness is life; and in the <qex>pathway</qex>
thereof is no death.</q> <rj><qau>Prov. xii. 28.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We tread the <qex>pathway</qex> arm in arm.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Patible</ent>⟦br⟧
